      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MORDECAI (1) ran well here over 1200m first-up, beaten 1.4 lengths despite being friendless in betting. Keeps the handy 2kg claim and is proven second-up. Has a good record here over this longer trip and will be fitter. TURN ME ROYALE (3) is third-up back plenty in grade. Has a key jockey switch to Wiggins, and the former Victorian is likely to appreciate the longer journey. Should be ready to show his best. MR SUGAR DADDY (5) deserved his heavily-bet Maiden win over at Townsville, but was flat there following in a stronger than this. Winning rider Thomas is reunited, and he can bounce back into the money. CASH ARTIST (2) resumed over 1400m at Rockhampton and needed the outing. Has come off a 60 win there over 1800m and is a second-up winner who placed his only run here over this longer trip. Quick improvement is likely.",
